Vanessa Jones' oldest child was regularly falling asleep to the television, and her youngest begged to go to Dairy Queen to get a toy advertised on TV. She and her friends are increasingly concerned about children's television -- the commercials, the programming and the fact that kids are just sitting there instead of playing. This weekend they are getting some help from an unlikely source : Nickelodeon, the No. 1 network for children, is replacing its usual Saturday afternoon lineup with a message encouraging young viewers to go outside and play. 